Patch Set 3:

Does it makes sense to queue discovery each time we call LNetPeerDiscovered() with negative result? E.g. it queues discovery if status is not uptodate and returns current peer status immediately. I am thinking about such code:
	if (!lnet_peer_is_uptodate(lp) &&
            lnet_peer_queue_for_discovery(lp)) {
		list_move(&lp->lp_dc_list, &the_lnet.ln_dc_request);
		wake_up(&the_lnet.ln_dc_waitq);
	}
which I've met in several places.
